The paper discusses the use of computational intelligence-based techniques for financial fraud detection, which falls under the category of cybersecurity (cs.CR). The paper also mentions the use of data mining methods and statistical and computational methods, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the classification of practices based on key aspects, which involves data analysis and organization, falling under the categories of data structures (cs.DS) and databases (cs.DB).
